description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are a registered Physiotherapist or Nurse with a keen interest in respiratory care, we want to hear from you&lt;/strong&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are delighted to share with you a number of Band 5 Respiratory Therapist opportunities in our Respiratory, High Dependency and Critical Care areas across the Northern Care Alliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trailblazing our range of new permanent respiratory practitioners available to band 5 physiotherapists OR nurses to support our ongoing work in response to the Covid-19 pandemic, these opportunities are available at our Salford, Oldham &amp; Bury Care Organisations where you will be based whilst providing support across all care organisations within the NCA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The roles are based in either our critical care, high dependency or respiratory wards and focus on supporting the multi-disciplinary teams in rehabilitating some of our most affected patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a passion for supporting and encouraging patients to regain their independence, be committed to providing individualised care plans and be a strong team player capable of working across professions to arrange the best care for your patient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A comprehensive competency based training programme will be provided by our team of clinical experts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexibility and willingness to work shifts across a 7 day week, 24 hour day is a must.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Victoria Dickens&lt;br /&gt;AHP Clinical Director&lt;br /&gt;ResourcingNCA@srft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
